title: Deer by a stream in the morning mist
description: A powerful male with large antlers was observed drinking in the early morning. The animal was calm and did not notice my presence from a distance of approximately 50 meters. Estimated age 8–10 years.

title: Fox hunting in the evening
description: The fox was actively hunting at the edge of the forest during sunset. A healthy individual with typical reddish fur. After a short while, it disappeared into dense vegetation.

title: Group of roe deer in a meadow
description: A group of three roe deer (one buck, two does) was observed calmly grazing on the eastern edge of the forest. The animals were in very good condition.

title: Wild boar sow with piglets in a wetland
description: A wild boar sow with five piglets was observed wading through mud in a wetland area. Tracks indicate nocturnal activity throughout the area. The piglets were very active.

title: Rare sighting of a Eurasian lynx!
description: An exceptional sighting of an adult Eurasian lynx! The animal was seen crossing a forest road at a higher altitude. Photo documentation was taken from a distance of approximately 80 meters. The protected area administrator was contacted.
